<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="13" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d13">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Argentine minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of Argentine</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-03-13"><hi rend="italic">March 13,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p rend="flushleft">Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>:</p>
                        <p>I have the profound sorrow of announcing to your excellency the demise of
                            the President of the Argentine Republic, the Most Excellent Dr. Don
                            Manuel Quintana, which took place in the early morning of yesterday.</p>
                        <p>His Excellency Don José Figueroa Alcorta, vice-president of the Republic,
                            has assumed the office of President, in accordance with the
                            constitution, for the term that was to be filled by the deceased
                            magistrate.</p>
                        <p>Be pleased to accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Epifanio
                            Portela.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>